.navbar.navbar-inverse.navbar-fixed-top
  .container
    .navbar-header
      button.navbar-toggle.collapsed(type='button', data-toggle='collapsed', data-target='#navbar', aria-expanded='false', aria-controls='navbar')
        span.sr-only Toggle Navigation
        span.icon-bar
        span.icon-bar
        span.icon-bar
      a.navbar-brand(href='#') Heath Journal Angular 2
    hj-login(*ngIf='user.isValid === false')
    hj-user-dropdown(*ngIf='user.isValid === true')
.jumbotron
  .container
    h1 Welcome to Health Journal Angular 2 
    p.title Trying logging in with the username - password
    ul
      li firstpres  - 1776
      li dmartin - dude
      li neckman - neckman
      li jvaughan3 - 6kids

    br
    p(*ngIf='user.isValid === true') You chose {{ user.fullname }}.  Excellent choice.  He shall serve us well if rescuers do not arrive in time to dig us out of the snow.
    p The take a look at the top right.  You should see the fullname of the user in a dropdown.  Drop it down and selelct Logout.
    p this is making a call to a backend service which is using a .json file for the data.
    p This also uses 3 components.  app.component, login.component (for the actual login section) and user-dropdown.component.  All three inject the AuthService and the app component subscribes to the userChanged obvservable to hide/show login/user dropdown.  Login calls into the auth service to perform the login.  User dropdown uses the auth service to perform a logout.  Both of these can result in the userChanged obvservable firing causing the app component to update.
